<h1>Identity Providers</h1>
<p>This user guide describes the Identity Providers Management related configurations available in the WSO2 Identity Server.</p>

<p>You can use the left hand side &quot;Main&quot; -> &quot;Identity&quot; -> &quot;Identity Providers&quot; menu to complete the below mentioned configuration details.</p>

<p>
    External Identity Providers that are trusted for various purposes are registered here by Administrators.
    These Identity Providers can be used for many different use cases.
    E.g. Federated login with an Identity Provider.
</p>
<p>
    Following  section describes adding and modifying Identity Providers in the system by an Administrator.
    Click on Main &gt; Identity &gt; Identity Providers &gt; Add to add Identity Providers to the system.
    You can also edit and delete registered Identity Providers by going to Main &gt; Identity &gt; Identity Providers
    &gt; List and clicking the corresponding links against them.
</p>
